	   <tr><td colspan=2>Thank you for stating that so well! I myself am a new player to this game. My highest lvl character is a 29 druid, and I just became the proud owner of my 20 lvl enchanter (I did lvl her there but it took forever it seems). I get a bit tired of the uber gaming. I was fortunate enough to know someone whose handmedowns I ended up with...which at lvl 6 meant I lived. But since then I have fought for everything and I tend to make my own way. I personally looked at this armor and thought *wow this stuff is pretty good*. But then my limited experience may have something to do with that. I will be incredibly excited when they get the other starting lvl armor quests up and running for the caster classes. My bard is decked out in her new starting armor (very green). More likely than not, you are right, Like face gear, head gear is hard to find for a caster. So are shoulders and feet. So my comment to those who take on this quest... GO FOR IT!!! The point of the game is to have fun. If you don;t have fun doing this quest... then stop. If you do however and gain a bit of experience on the way ... EXCELLENT!&nbsp;&nbsp;Good luck and may there always be a sower nearby:)<br><br>Elliara Kelerin<br>Druid of the 29th cycle<br>Terris-Thule server <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
