	   <tr><td colspan=2>Why some of these items, even though they are not very good, may be helpful is when there is a slot not very found for a certain class.<br><br>For example, pure casters that are poor and actually playing the game instead of being an auction master or ebaying @#%^ may not find easy.<br><br>Not saying helms are not easy to find, there is Runed Cowl, Platinum Blue Diamond Tiara, and others but something like shoulders, cloak, sash etc. might be helpful.<br><br>So before you diss this armor, think of the less fortunate players who may think this is amazing armor, because in its own essence, it is really pretty good if you look at it from a level thirty-fourty standpoint.<br><br>Not everyone has tens of thousands of platinum pieces stored away in their bank, along with kael uber loot and ssra weps. So just remember, when you diss this stuff, think of what you were like at level thirty or so with your first character, and maybe you will re-evaluate your thinking pattern.<br><br>For me, yeah, I wouldn't be caught dead in this, because the path in EverQuest was different, at level fifty-three on my warrior I was in full champions, crescent blades of luclin, frostbringer, cloak of flames and other very high end equiptment. My path was an auctioneer, a trader, but I always respect the items of others.<br><br>So basically, just don't diss this armor, it will make lots of enchanters feel fortunate and &quot;decked out&quot; becuase what do you know, it could be replacing a cloth cap!<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
